sec.p:
Measurements of BMI (kg/m2, defined as body weight divided by height squared), waist circumference (cm), systolic blood pressure (SBP, mmHg), and diastolic blood pressure (DBP, mmHg) were recorded. Height was measured in stocking feet, and weight was measured in light indoor clothing. The waist circumference was measured using a tape measure wrapped around the waist in line with the navel at the minimum respiration. Blood pressure was measured with a standard sphygmomanometer or an automated device by medical staff at each local institute. Blood samples were collected from each participant after an eight-hour or more fasting period to measure the fasting plasma glucose (FPG) (mg/dL), low-density lipoprotein cholesterol (LDL-C; mg/dL), high-density lipoprotein cholesterol (HDL-C; mg/dL), and triglyceride (mg/dL) levels. Based on these measurements, the following obesity indices were calculated, converting the units from mg/dL to mmol/L when necessary.
